Calculator: -
During my academic journey at the university, I have had the privilege of delving into the world of web development under the insightful guidance of my lectures. One of the practical applications of my learning has been the development of a calculator using HTML and CSS. This project not only allowed me to reinforce the theoretical concepts discussed in class but also provided a hands-on experience in translating these skills into a tangible web application. Through this project, I gained a deeper understanding of structuring web content with HTML and styling it with CSS, ensuring both functionality and an aesthetically pleasing user interface. The guidance from my lectures played a crucial role in shaping my approach and refining the code, making this experience a valuable contribution to my growing skill set in web development.

Html code:-
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Calculator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1><b>Calculator</b></h1>
    <form action="" name="cal">
        <input type="text" name="display" style="width: 350px; height: 90px; background-color: #4c555c;color: rgb(7, 255, 164);"><br>
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="0" onclick="cal.display.value += '0'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="1" onclick="cal.display.value += '1'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="2" onclick="cal.display.value += '2'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="+" onclick="cal.display.value += '+'" style=" background-color: #cc7e11;"><br>
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="3" onclick="cal.display.value += '3'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="4" onclick="cal.display.value += '4'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="5" onclick="cal.display.value += '5'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="-" onclick="cal.display.value += '-'" style="background-color: #c500f7;"><br>
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="6" onclick="cal.display.value += '6'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="7" onclick="cal.display.value += '7'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="8" onclick="cal.display.value += '8'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="*" onclick="cal.display.value += '*'" style="background-color: #fa0000;"><br>
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="9" onclick="cal.display.value += '9'">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="C" onclick="cal.display.value =''" style="background-color:#fff200;">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="=" onclick="cal.display.value =eval(cal.display.value)" style="background-color: #00fa08;">
        <input class="btn" type="button" value="&#247;" onclick="cal.display.value += '/'" style="background-color: #1f47c9;">

    </form>
</body>
</html>



CSS code:-

body{
    margin: 0px;
    padding: 0px;
    background-color: #00ffee;
    color: #ff00d9;
    text-align: center;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: cover;
    background:url(background.jpg);
    height: 100vh;
}
h1{
    font-size: 75px;
}

input{
    width: 75px;
    height: 55px;
    font-size: 35px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin: 10px;
    background-color: white;
    color: rgb(0, 0, 0);
    border-style: none;

}

.btn:hover{
    background-color:rgb(0, 34, 255);
    cursor: pointer;
}




